  "texts": [
    "• In the dimension of Communication Policy, current works often assume a binary communication action regarding whether or not to communicate with other agents (or a specific agent).",
    "However, communication actions can be more fine-grained and descriptive.",
    "For instance, agents might opt to send only a portion of their messages due to uncertainty or lack of confidence.",
    "Additionally, a communication action could be defined more specifically, such as communicate with others if the budget exceeds a predetermined threshold.",
    "Thus, a communication policy can encompass a variety of communication actions, tailored to align with human heuristics and specific system requirements."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}